<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n821" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφι-χέομαι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χέω</span>), ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφεχεόμην</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφεχύμην,
            ἀμφέχυτο</span>, pass. aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφεχύθην</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pour</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be
            diffused</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shed around, embrace;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πάρος κόνιν ἀμφιχυθῆναι</span>, before the
          dust (stirred by the feet of Ajax immediately in advance) could ‘pour
          (rise) round’ him (Odysseus), <i><span class="en">Il.
            23.763</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀμφιχυθεὶς πατέρα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 16.214</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἀμφεχέοντο</span> (‘thronged around’) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καὶ
            ἠσπάζοντ᾽ Ὀδυσῆα</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            22.498</span></i>; metaph., of sounds (<i><span class="en">Il.
            2.41</span></i>), feelings (<i><span class="en">Od. 4.716</span></i>),
          sleep (<i><span class="en">Il. 14.253</span></i>).</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
